    <briefdescription>
<para>ARM(R) SysTick driver. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This driver configures ARM(R) SysTick as a free-running timer. This timer is used to generate delays and pool for timeouts. Only relatively short timeouts are supported. The SysTick works on 64MHz and is 24-bit wide. This means that it overflows around 4 times per second and around 250 microseconds will be the highest supported time in the library. As it is hard to detect if the overflow is generated without using interrupts, the maximum delay range is halved for safety reasons. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
